gm-method: prd-resolve matches the id field fuzzily, not exactly. Dispatching prd-resolve with id 'acp-daemon-spawn' silently resolved the unrelated row 'security-auth-gating' (returned {resolved: security-auth-gating}). ALWAYS read the prd-resolve response {resolved:<id>} and confirm it equals the intended id; if it diverges, the witness landed on the wrong row. When the intended rows are absent from prd_pending entirely, they were resolved in a PRIOR session and re-resolving is unnecessary; verify by reading the live pending list rather than blind-resolving. Audit-style work where target rows are already closed = the deliverable is the witnessed findings returned to the caller, not a re-resolution.